FT  08 MAY 91 / London Arena
THE London Arena, the conference, sporting and conference venue in
Docklands, has gone into receivership with debts of more than Pounds 20m.
Security Pacific, the project's principal banker, yesterday appointed Mr
Jonathan Phillips and Mr Mark Homan, partners in Price Waterhouse, as
administrative receivers of Arena Developments (Europe) Ltd, the majority of
which is owned by Mr Frank Warren, the boxing promoter, and his partner, Mr
John Botros.
